        {
            "_id": "V4gCwuSRavQHpA2w",
            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-monster-core-2.Actor.n40ubwOuMGF7HHZ6.Item.k7Sj3Od8RCFh7XNG"
            },
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Agonized Howl",
            "sort": 700000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The unrisen howls in pain at its cursed existence. Creatures within a @Template[type:emanation|distance:30] take @Damage[10d8[mental]|options:area-damage] damage with a @Check[will|dc:32|basic] save. The unrisen can't use Agonized Howl again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Agonized Howl]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "auditory",
                        "mental",
                        "occult"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "HVMsEifpM7BsJpjO",
            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-monster-core-2.Actor.n40ubwOuMGF7HHZ6.Item.HEeo8Cny4nmBNF1e"
            },
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Awful Approach",
            "sort": 800000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per 10 minutes</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The unrisen reshapes its grotesque form to move swiftly. It Strides twice. Any living creature that can see the unrisen during this movement must succeed at a @Check[fortitude|dc:29] save or be @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} (or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} on a critical failure); this is a mental and visual effect.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "PT10M"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "pjO2205EJWqHHVqQ",
            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-monster-core-2.Actor.n40ubwOuMGF7HHZ6.Item.LHoHnZupawH74oRD"
            },
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Death Grip",
            "sort": 900000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The unrisen has a living creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed] or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained]</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The unrisen attempts to destroy its victim's life force so it shares in the unrisen's fate. The creature must succeed at a @Check[fortitude|dc:32] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Doomed]{Doomed 1}. While the curse lasts, the creature regains only half as many HP from effects with both the healing and vitality traits; if it dies, any attempt to raise it from the dead causes it to return as an unrisen. The curse ends automatically if the creature's doomed value is reduced to 0.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "curse",
                        "occult"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "lYcdAd4M8q9OydxX",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Show the Horror",
            "sort": 1000000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The Mistake has used rise again within the previous hour</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The Mistake grabs onto its chest and tugs it open, cracking ribs and tearing flesh to give a glimpse of the horrible @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Vile Remnant] lodged inside of it. All creatures within 30 feet must attempt a @Check[will|dc:32|options:area-effect,inflicts:frightened,inflicts:slowed] save with the following results. The Mistake can't Show the Horror again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Show the Horror]]{1d4 rounds}.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unsettled by the sight and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2} and feels something shift in its own chest, as if a similarly shaped horror was within its own ribcage and twitching in delight at seeing its twin in another place. The affected creature can't reduce its frightened condition below 1 as long as The Mistake remains active and within 60 feet.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 3}, and the creature continues to feel that awful chest twitch any time thereafter it becomes frightened. The creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} whenever it's frightened as it uses one of its actions to grip at its chest and worry about the implications of what might be inside of it; this curse has an unlimited duration.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "curse",
                        "emotion",
                        "fear",
                        "mental",
                        "occult",
                        "visual"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
